{"bookId": "67656ccf18ff438b6c18cc4c", "moduleId": "67656ccf18ff438b6c18cc4c", "subjectId": "67656cd518ff438b6c18cc4d", "chapterId": "67656cd618ff438b6c18cc53", "subject": "Physics", "chapter": "Mechanics 2", "count": 8, "questions": [{"id": 0, "subject": "Physics", "chapter": "Mechanics 2", "exam": "Engineering", "examName": "Must Do Top Qs of JEE Main 2024", "q": "Two metallic wires <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>Q</mi></math> have same volume and are made up of same material. If their area of cross sections are in the ratio <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mo>:</mo><mo> </mo><mn>1</mn></math> and force <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>F</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math> is applied to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi></math>, an extension of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>∆</mo><mi>l</mi></math> is produced. The force which is required to produce same extension in <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Q</mi></math> is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>F</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math>. The value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msub><mi>F</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mrow><mo> </mo><msub><mi>F</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow></mfrac></math> is ______.", "options": ["A", "B", "C", "D"], "answer": 0, "solution": "<p>The formula for Young's modulus is given by</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtable columnalign=\"right center left\" columnspacing=\"0px\"><mtr><mtd><mi>Y</mi></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mfrac><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mi>F</mi><mi>A</mi></mfrac></mstyle><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>∆</mo><mi>l</mi></mrow><mi>l</mi></mfrac></mstyle></mfrac></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mfrac><mrow><mi>F</mi><mi>l</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>A</mi><mo>∆</mo><mi>l</mi></mrow></mfrac></mtd></mtr></mtable></math></p><p>From above equation, it follows that</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>Δ</mi><mi>l</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>F</mi><mi>l</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>A</mi><mi>Y</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo> </mo><mo> </mo><mo> </mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>1</mn></mfenced></math></p><p>Again, volume of the wire is given by</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>V</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>A</mi><mi>l</mi><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>⇒</mo><mi>l</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>V</mi><mi>A</mi></mfrac></math></p><p>Hence, from equation (1),</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>∆</mo><mi>l</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>F</mi><mi>V</mi></mrow><mrow><msup><mi>A</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>Y</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo> </mo><mo> </mo><mo> </mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>2</mn></mfenced></math></p><p>As, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>Y</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>V</mi></math> is the same for both the wires,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>∆</mo><mi>l</mi><mo>∝</mo><mfrac><mi>F</mi><mrow><mo> </mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p>Hence, for two wires, it can be written that</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>∆</mo><msub><mi>l</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mrow><mrow><mo>∆</mo><msub><mi>l</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msub><mi>F</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mrow><mo> </mo><msubsup><mi>A</mi><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></msubsup></mrow></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mfrac><msubsup><mi>A</mi><mn>2</mn><mn>2</mn></msubsup><mrow><mo> </mo><msub><mi>F</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow></mfrac><mo> </mo><mo> </mo><mo> </mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>3</mn></mfenced></math></p><p>As <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>∆</mo><msub><mi>l</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mo>∆</mo><msub><mi>l</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math>, from equation (3), it follows that</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>F</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo> </mo><msubsup><mi>A</mi><mn>2</mn><mn>2</mn></msubsup><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>F</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo> </mo><msubsup><mi>A</mi><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></msubsup><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>⇒</mo><mfrac><msub><mi>F</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mrow><mo> </mo><msub><mi>F</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msubsup><mi>A</mi><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></msubsup><mrow><mo> </mo><msubsup><mi>A</mi><mn>2</mn><mn>2</mn></msubsup></mrow></mfrac><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>=</mo><msup><mfenced><mfrac><mn>4</mn><mn>1</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>=</mo><mn>16</mn></math></p>", "difficulty": "Easy", "source": "JEE Main 2024 (29 Jan Shift 2)", "_marksId": "6682bd6eba0e94a3c4025c98"}, {"id": 0, "subject": "Physics", "chapter": "Mechanics 2", "exam": "Engineering", "examName": "Must Do Top Qs of JEE Main 2024", "q": "<p>Each of three blocks <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mo>,</mo><mo> </mo><mi>Q</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi></math> shown in figure has a mass of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mo> </mo><mi>kg</mi></math>. Each of the wire <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>B</mi></math> has cross-sectional area <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>005</mn><mo> </mo><msup><mi>cm</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math> and Young's modulus <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>11</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi><mo> </mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math>. Neglecting friction, the longitudinal strain on wire <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>B</mi></math> is _____ <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></msup></math>. (Take <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>g</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mo> </mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math>)</p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/c5c645cb-287d-4bb6-910d-54dcb9d3b592.png\" style=\"width: 250px; height: 156px;\"/>", "options": ["A", "B", "C", "D"], "answer": 0, "solution": "<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/681e0685-f4cb-4578-9dee-b28fa2dc0bb1.png\" style=\"width: 250px; height: 161px;\"/></p><p>Acceleration of the system, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>g</mi></mrow><mn>9</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>10</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mo> </mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math></p><p>Now, for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi></math> we can write</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>30</mn><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>T</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>×</mo><mi>a</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><msub><mi>T</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>20</mn><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi></math></p><p>Therefore, strain developed in wire <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>B</mi></math>, </p><p> <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>strain</mtext><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mtext> stress </mtext><mi>Y</mi></mfrac><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><msub><mi>T</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mi>A</mi></mfrac></mstyle><mi>Y</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>20</mn><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>005</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac></mstyle><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>11</mn></msup></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></msup></math></p>", "difficulty": "Easy", "source": "JEE Main 2024 (30 Jan Shift 1)", "_marksId": "6682bd6eba0e94a3c4025c9b"}, {"id": 0, "subject": "Physics", "chapter": "Mechanics 2", "exam": "Engineering", "examName": "Must Do Top Qs of JEE Main 2024", "q": "<p>Two blocks of mass <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><mi>kg</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mo> </mo><mi>kg</mi></math> are connected by a metal wire going over a smooth pulley as shown in figure. The radius of wire is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow></msup><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math> and Young's modulus of the metal is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>11</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi><mo> </mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math>. The longitudinal strain developed in the wire is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mi>α</mi><mi>π</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>. The value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>α</mi></math> is _____. [Use <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>g</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mo> </mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math>)</p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/01a36e11-5509-4153-ae5e-feae4cbc8268.png\" style=\"width: 250px; height: 234px;\"/>", "options": ["A", "B", "C", "D"], "answer": 0, "solution": "<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/01a36e11-5509-4153-ae5e-feae4cbc8268.png\" style=\"width: 250px; height: 234px;\"/></p><p>For the given system, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><msub><mi>m</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><msub><mi>m</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow><mrow><msub><mi>m</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>m</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow></mfrac></mfenced><mi>g</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>80</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi></math></p><p>Area of the wire, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>π</mi><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>16</mn><mi>π</mi><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>−</mo><mn>10</mn></mrow></msup><mo> </mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math></p><p>Strain <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>Δ</mi><mi mathvariant=\"script\">l</mi></mrow><mi mathvariant=\"script\">l</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>F</mi><mrow><mi>A</mi><mi>Y</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>T</mi><mrow><mi>A</mi><mi>Y</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mfrac><mn>80</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mrow><mn>16</mn><mi>π</mi><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>−</mo><mn>10</mn></mrow></msup><mo>×</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>11</mn></msup></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mn>12</mn><mi>π</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><mi>α</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>12</mn></math></p>", "difficulty": "Medium", "source": "JEE Main 2024 (31 Jan Shift 2)", "_marksId": "6682bd6eba0e94a3c4025c9c"}, {"id": 0, "subject": "Physics", "chapter": "Mechanics 2", "exam": "Engineering", "examName": "Must Do Top Qs of JEE Main 2024", "q": "Match List-I with List-II :\n$\\begin{array}{|c|c|c|c|}\n\\hline & \\text { List-I } & & \\text { List-II } \\\\\n\\hline \\text { (A) } & \\text { A force that restores an elastic body of unit area to its original state } & \\text { (I) } & \\text { Bulk modulus } \\\\\n\\hline \\text { (B) } & \\text { Two equal and opposite forces parallel to opposite faces } & \\text { (II) } & \\text { Young's modulus } \\\\\n\\hline \\text { (C) } & \\begin{array}{l}\n\\text { Forces perpendicular everywhere to the surface per unit area } \\\\\n\\text { same everywhere }\n\\end{array} & \\text { (III) } & \\text { Stress } \\\\\n\\hline \\text { (D) } & \\text { Two equal and opposite forces perpendicular to opposite faces } & \\text { (IV) } & \\text { Shear modulus } \\\\\n\\hline\n\\end{array}$\nChoose the correct answer from the options given below :", "options": ["(A)-(IV), (B)-(II), (C)-(III), (D)-(I)", "(A)-(III), (B)-(IV), (C)-(I), (D)-(II)", "(A)-(II), (B)-(IV), (C)-(I), (D)-(III)", "(A)-(III), (B)-(I), (C)-(II), (D)-(IV)"], "answer": 1, "solution": "(1) stress $=\\frac{F_{\\text {restoring }}}{A}$\nIf $\\mathrm{A}=1$\nStress $=F_{\\text {restoring }}$\n(A)-(III)\n(2)<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/MBXI-76aDG5GkDVht5jNZPT9lkqbIB7_SsPktIf9JtU.original.fullsize.png\"><br />(B)-(IV)\n(3)<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/7NFE3WRFDhA_FQKy6_lRInzuZkghDIRP0plkfqb3Tsk.original.fullsize.png\"><br />(C)-(I)\n(4)<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/USk5Xj11TYZZ9lBycPn4WOL6XS2l3QRx5ELwwekcoB8.original.fullsize.png\"><br />(D)-(II)", "difficulty": "Medium", "source": "JEE Main 2024 (05 Apr Shift 2)", "_marksId": "6644671f970e6e9ab542d068"}, {"id": 0, "subject": "Physics", "chapter": "Mechanics 2", "exam": "Engineering", "examName": "Must Do Top Qs of JEE Main 2024", "q": "<p>If average depth of an ocean is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4000</mn><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math> and the bulk modulus of water is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>9</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi><mo> </mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math>, then fractional compression <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>Δ</mi><mi>V</mi></mrow><mi>V</mi></mfrac></math> of water at the bottom of ocean is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>α</mi><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math>. The value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>α</mi></math> is _______, (Given, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mo> </mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mo>,</mo><mo> </mo><mi>ρ</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1000</mn><mo> </mo><mi>kg</mi><mo> </mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup></math>)</p>", "options": ["A", "B", "C", "D"], "answer": 0, "solution": "<p>The formula to calculate the Bulk modulus is given by</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>B</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>∆</mo><mi>P</mi></mrow><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mo>∆</mo><mi>V</mi></mrow><mi>V</mi></mfrac></mfenced></mfrac><mo> </mo><mo> </mo><mo> </mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>1</mn></mfenced></math></p><p>From equation (1), the fractional compression in volume may be obtained as follows:</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtable columnalign=\"right center left\" columnspacing=\"0px\"><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mi>Δ</mi><mi>V</mi></mrow><mi>V</mi></mfrac></mfenced></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mfrac><mrow><mo>∆</mo><mi>P</mi></mrow><mi>B</mi></mfrac></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mfrac><mrow><mi>ρ</mi><mi>g</mi><mo>∆</mo><mi>h</mi></mrow><mi>B</mi></mfrac><mo> </mo><mo> </mo><mo> </mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>2</mn></mfenced></mtd></mtr></mtable></math></p><p>From equation (2) it follows that</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtable columnalign=\"right center left\" columnspacing=\"0px\"><mtr><mtd><mfenced close=\"|\" open=\"|\"><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mo>∆</mo><mi>V</mi></mrow><mi>V</mi></mfrac></mfenced></mrow></mfenced></mtd><mtd><mo>=</mo></mtd><mtd><mfrac><mrow><mn>1000</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>4000</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>9</mn></msup></mrow></mfrac></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd><mtd><mo>⇒</mo></mtd><mtd><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mo>∆</mo><mi>V</mi></mrow><mi>V</mi></mfrac></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mtd></mtr></mtable></math></p><p>Hence, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>α</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></math>.</p>", "difficulty": "Medium", "source": "JEE Main 2024 (27 Jan Shift 1)", "_marksId": "6682bd6eba0e94a3c4025c9a"}, {"id": 0, "subject": "Physics", "chapter": "Mechanics 2", "exam": "Engineering", "examName": "Must Do Top Qs of JEE Main 2024", "q": "The position, velocity and acceleration of a particle executing simple harmonic motion are found to have magnitudes of $4 \\mathrm{~m}, 2 \\mathrm{~ms}^{-1}$ and $16 \\mathrm{~ms}^{-2}$ at a certain instant. The amplitude of the motion is $\\sqrt{x}, \\mathrm{~m}$ where $x$ is ________", "options": ["A", "B", "C", "D"], "answer": 0, "solution": "$\\begin{aligned} & x=4 \\mathrm{~m}, V=2 \\mathrm{~m} / \\mathrm{s}, \\mathrm{a}=16 \\mathrm{~m} / \\mathrm{s}^2 \\\\ & |\\mathrm{a}|=\\omega^2 \\mathrm{x} \\\\ & \\Rightarrow 16=\\omega^2(4) \\\\ & \\omega=2 \\mathrm{rad} / \\mathrm{s} \\\\ & \\mathrm{v}=\\omega \\sqrt{\\mathrm{A}^2-\\mathrm{x}^2} \\\\ & A=\\sqrt{\\frac{\\mathrm{v}^2}{\\omega^2}+\\mathrm{x}^2} \\Rightarrow \\mathrm{A}=\\sqrt{\\frac{4}{4}+16} \\\\ & A=\\sqrt{17} \\mathrm{~m}\\end{aligned}$", "difficulty": "Easy", "source": "JEE Main 2024 (09 Apr Shift 1)", "_marksId": "66446751970e6e9ab542d23a"}, {"id": 0, "subject": "Physics", "chapter": "Mechanics 2", "exam": "Engineering", "examName": "Must Do Top Qs of JEE Main 2024", "q": "A particle performs simple harmonic motion with amplitude <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi></math>. Its speed is increased to three times at an instant when its displacement is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>A</mi></mrow><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math>. The new amplitude of motion is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>n</mi><mi>A</mi></mrow><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math>. The value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi></math> is _____.", "options": ["A", "B", "C", "D"], "answer": 0, "solution": "<p>Speed in SHM in terms of displacement is given by, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>ω</mi><msqrt><msup><mi>A</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt></math>.</p><p>at <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>A</mi></mrow><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math>, we get</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>ω</mi><msqrt><msup><mi>A</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>A</mi></mrow><mn>3</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msqrt><mn>5</mn></msqrt><mi>A</mi><mi>ω</mi></mrow><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math></p><p>Let the new amplitude be<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mi>A</mi><mo>'</mo></math></p><p>Then, </p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi><mo>'</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>v</mi><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>⇒</mo><mi>ω</mi><msqrt><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>A</mi><mo>'</mo></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>A</mi></mrow><mn>3</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>5</mn></msqrt><mi>A</mi><mi>ω</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><mi>A</mi><mo>'</mo><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>7</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mi>A</mi></math></p><p>Therefore, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>7</mn></math>. </p>", "difficulty": "Medium", "source": "JEE Main 2024 (31 Jan Shift 1)", "_marksId": "6682bd74ba0e94a3c4025cbd"}, {"id": 0, "subject": "Physics", "chapter": "Mechanics 2", "exam": "Engineering", "examName": "Must Do Top Qs of JEE Main 2024", "q": "<p>A simple pendulum is placed at a place where its distance from the earth's surface is equal to the radius of the earth. If the length of the string is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math>, then the time period of small oscillations will be _________<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi></math>.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>[</mo></math>take <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>g</mi><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>π</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mo> </mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math>]</p>", "options": ["A", "B", "C", "D"], "answer": 0, "solution": "<blockquote><p>Acceleration due to gravity at surface of earth, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>g</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>G</mi><mi>M</mi></mrow><msup><mi>R</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></math>.</p><p>Now, at distance <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi></math> from the surface of the earth, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>g</mi><mo>'</mo></msup><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>G</mi><mi>M</mi></mrow><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>R</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>R</mi></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>g</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math></p><p>Therefore,<br/><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>π</mi><msqrt><mfrac><mi>l</mi><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mi>g</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac></mstyle></mfrac></msqrt></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><mi>T</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>π</mi><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow><mrow><mo> </mo><mi>g</mi></mrow></mfrac></msqrt></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><mi>T</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>π</mi><mfrac><mn>4</mn><mi>π</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi></math></p></blockquote>", "difficulty": "Medium", "source": "JEE Main 2024 (30 Jan Shift 2)", "_marksId": "6682bd74ba0e94a3c4025cbf"}]}